                      "menu_id": 20,
                      "name": "Очканатлан",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "After the",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "text",
                      "ep_id": 7089,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/10/12/237301566/93cd2bc9b90c8b87b1f8cbdbe95b4b9d_1090730713764694732.png",
                      "menu_id": 20,
                      "name": "Катаклизм в Каэнри'ах",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": ", Titu and a group of people went to Ochkanatlan to look for the legendary Jade of Return, which could destroy the Abyss. Of the entire group, only one person survived, and Titu himself died on the ship \"Tonatiuh.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 7017,
                      "icon_url": "",
                      "name": "Манку",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Titu calls Manqu his brother.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "In reality, Manqu is a phlogiston projection of Waxaklahun Ubah Kan.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 7297,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/11/21/237301566/54803da47d93bdbc9dd14b8e83897961_3756506357916964918.png",
                      "menu_id": 10,
                      "name": "Вашаклахун Уба Кан",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "After Titu's death on \"Tonatiuh,\" Waxaklahun Ubah Kan used his image for his own purposes. \"Titu\" had several past lives and memories of the past lives, but he was not in any of them. \"Titu's\" life was like a dream in which he could not control his body. When the Sage of the Stolen Flame dissolved, \"Titu\" awoke from his sleep and heard the call of the Lord of the Night.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:#ffffff"
